{"key":"processedPost-9497340","value":{"id":9497340,"first":9496362,"last":9501784,"when":1230321670,"utime":"12/26/08 10:01 PM","cleanedPost":"If you're making a mini-greenhouse, get a good analog hygrometer, and then use a good cycle timer to operate your humidifier.&nbsp; I tried all the major brands of humidistats a few years ago, including the expensive ones, and none can stand up to the spore loads we get in mycology.&nbsp;  Use timers to dial in your humidifiers and adjust them weekly or so as the ambient conditions change.<br />For terrariums, use perlite humidification and holes per the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shotgun terrarium tek</a>, and you'll be fine.<br />RR"}}